flagship release, okay?

01:00.602 --> 01:03.146
And I have
the perfect anchor song,

01:03.229 --> 01:05.565
a cute, sweet little
number for my boo.

01:05.648 --> 01:06.733
Okay, but which boo?

01:06.816 --> 01:08.485
The new boo
or "original recipe" boo?

01:08.568 --> 01:09.736
Okay,
get out her business.

01:09.819 --> 01:11.154
First of all,
don't listen to Becky, okay?

01:11.237 --> 01:12.363
Devon is a real one.

01:12.447 --> 01:13.698
You got a good one
on your hands.

01:13.782 --> 01:15.617
Okay, enough; enough of
the chitter-chatter, guppies.

01:15.700 --> 01:16.785
Let's get back to work.
Come on.

01:16.868 --> 01:17.952
Come on, come on.

01:18.036 --> 01:19.746
Aunt Cookie?

01:19.829 --> 01:21.581
Keisha?
Uh, what are you doing here?

01:21.664 --> 01:22.749
Is Carol okay?

01:22.832 --> 01:23.958
I don't think so.

01:26.461 --> 01:28.588
Come here.

01:28.671 --> 01:29.756
She got two other guys
in her business.

01:29.839 --> 01:31.174
Oh, my God.

01:31.257 --> 01:33.635
She won't let me come over,
and she won't leave the house.

01:33.718 --> 01:35.095
Where your brother and sister?

01:35.178 --> 01:36.471
At Aunt Candace's.

01:36.554 --> 01:38.056
Please.

01:38.139 --> 01:39.974
I'm worried
she's gonna kill herself.

01:42.477 --> 01:44.229
Hey, I gotta make a run.

01:44.312 --> 01:47.357
♪ ♪

01:50.443 --> 01:52.403
