you can say in front of me.

03:48.144 --> 03:49.312
We don't keep secrets.

03:50.939 --> 03:55.109
Then out of respect for you,
I'm gonna keep it real.

03:55.193 --> 03:56.319
I'd appreciate that.

03:56.402 --> 03:59.656
The song you want for Yana

03:59.739 --> 04:02.158
is some...

04:02.242 --> 04:04.535
"reserved for Beyoncé"
caliber heat.

04:04.619 --> 04:05.703
You feel me?

04:05.787 --> 04:06.829
Okay, Destiny,

04:06.913 --> 04:09.165
Yana is an extremely
talented singer.

04:09.249 --> 04:11.042
I'm sure you have
some song up your sleeve--

04:11.125 --> 04:13.461
No offense,
but I saw your girl here bomb

04:13.544 --> 04:15.129
on the Music Weekly show.

04:15.213 --> 04:17.507
Destiny,
a lot of artists have bombed

04:17.590 --> 04:19.050
on their way up to the top,
and you know that.

04:19.133 --> 04:22.220
Okay, that was
Lana Del Rey on SNL bad.

04:22.553 --> 04:23.763
Wow.

04:23.846 --> 04:24.889
Your girl's
in a deficit right now.

04:24.973 --> 04:26.808
All right, okay.
I get it.

04:26.891 --> 04:29.519
I am inexperienced,
and I have a lot to prove.

04:29.602 --> 04:31.437
But can I ask you something?

04:31.771 --> 04:32.897
When you started out,

04:32.981 --> 04:35.566
how did you let everybody know
that you were for real?

04:35.900 --> 04:37.777
I wrote my ass off.

04:37.860 --> 04:39.279
And that's exactly
what I'm gonna do.

04:39.362 --> 04:40.446
Uh...

04:40.530 --> 04:42.448
Yana, you're very talented,

04:42.532 --> 04:44.951
but we need something iconic
to launch you.

04:45.034 --> 04:47.036
We will pay you top dollar.

04:47.120 --> 04:48.204
No.

04:48.288 --> 04:50.373
If this song is supposed to

04:50.456 --> 04:53.418
represent me as an artist,
then I need to write it.

04:53.501 --> 04:54.961
It needs to come from me.

04:55.044 --> 04:57.213
And with all due respect,
Ms. DeVereaux,

04:57.297 --> 04:59.382
I know my voice
better than anybody else,

04:59.465 --> 05:00.675
and I know how to represent it.

05:02.677 --> 05:04.470
That's what you would do,
Lucious.

05:04.554 --> 05:08.433
♪ ♪

05:08.766 --> 05:09.934
Absolutely.

05:10.018 --> 05:13.271
In all truth, I mean,
anyone that doubts Yana--

05:13.354 --> 05:15.982
and that's pretty much
everybody in the damn industry

05:16.065 --> 05:18.818
right now--is not
really worthy of writing

05:18.901 --> 05:20.737
a song for her,
with all due respect.

05:21.863 --> 05:22.947
Come on.

05:23.031 --> 05:24.115
Cancel the rest of
the meetings.

05:24.198 --> 05:26.034
We're out.
Come on.

05:28.494 --> 05:29.746
Quit playing around, Lucious.

05:29.829 --> 05:31.164
We gotta finish this album.

05:31.247 --> 05:32.707
Just give me a minute.

05:33.708 --> 05:35.543
- Yo, what was that?
- Wait, play that again.

05:35.626 --> 05:36.711
Hit record, fool.

05:36.794 --> 05:37.795
I got you.

05:37.879 --> 05:43.134
♪ ♪

05:43.217 --> 05:44.594
Remember to stay above the mix.

05:44.677 --> 05:49.724
♪ ♪

05:49.807 --> 05:51.351
Spit some bars, Lucious.

05:51.434 --> 05:53.478
♪ Look, I don't need
no introduction ♪

05:53.561 --> 05:55.313
♪ Finna do it
big as Paul Bunyan ♪

05:55.396 --> 05:57.857
♪ Flows be hitting hard enough
to give concussions ♪

05:57.940 --> 05:59.025
♪ Pardon the interruption ♪

05:59.108 --> 06:00.526
♪ But I don't pull
no punches ♪

06:00.610 --> 06:02.445
♪ And I really need
to kill a beat ♪

06:02.528 --> 06:04.155
♪ A little keys
and some percussion ♪

06:04.238 --> 06:06.657
♪ Like it's nothing,
you already know who it is ♪

06:06.741 --> 06:08.701
♪ They ain't never "Lyon"
when they saying ♪

06:08.785 --> 06:11.204
♪ "Lucious equipped,"
living legend in the making ♪

06:11.287 --> 06:12.747
♪ Yeah,
I'm flipping the script ♪

06:12.830 --> 06:14.082
♪ Made it to the studio ♪

06:14.165 --> 06:16.084
♪ From slangin' dope
as a kid, dig ♪

06:16.167 --> 06:17.668
♪ Selling CDs out the trunk ♪

06:17.752 --> 06:19.003
♪ $7, what you want ♪

06:19.087 --> 06:20.671
♪ I could never fake
the funk ♪

06:20.755 --> 06:21.964
♪ Know you smell me ♪

06:22.048 --> 06:23.466
