07:01.587 --> 07:02.588
Did they get it?

07:02.672 --> 07:04.424
Uh, yeah, no,
the last scene

07:04.507 --> 07:05.716
was actually amazing.

07:05.800 --> 07:08.010
Great, that's one less thing
to worry about.

07:08.094 --> 07:09.137
What do you mean?

07:09.220 --> 07:10.721
The latest tracking numbers
came in,

07:10.805 --> 07:11.889
and they're garbage.

07:12.932 --> 07:15.017
Who's bright idea was it to set
the release date for our movie

07:15.101 --> 07:16.394
on the same day
as a Marvel movie?

07:16.477 --> 07:18.271
Oh, marketing said that it was
good counterprogramming.

07:18.354 --> 07:19.814
People love an underdog story,

07:19.897 --> 07:20.898
but if nobody knows
we're out there,

07:20.982 --> 07:22.066
it won't matter.

07:22.150 --> 07:23.693
Find a way to get
people talking.

07:23.776 --> 07:24.944
Andre, I'm not a Kardashian.

07:25.027 --> 07:26.154
I can't just get
the Internet to do

07:26.237 --> 07:27.321
whatever you want it to do.

07:27.405 --> 07:28.698
You showed me how far

07:28.781 --> 07:29.866
you were willing to go
to wrangle

07:29.949 --> 07:31.367
that recording contract
out of me.

07:31.451 --> 07:33.202
